sentences: Lauren Nicole Platt (born 7 October 1997) is an English television presenter, singer and actress.
Platt was born on 7 October 1997 in Billericay, Essex, but spent ten years living in Spain.
In 2010, she auditioned for the role of Louise Mitchell on EastEnders, but lost out to Brittany Papple.
In 2011, she was the runner-up of the local talent contest The Essex Factor and in 2012, competed in Open Mic UK.
